s/external-disjoints.obo --reasoner ELK --output /tmp/opencode/external-disjoints-reasoned.owl\n+```\n+\n+Signed: @dragon-ai-agent\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,1 @@\n+Added the requested disjointness axiom between `multicellular organism` and `organism substance`; changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+## Summary\n+\n+This change addresses issue #2421 by adding an explicit disjointness axiom between:\n+\n+- `UBERON:0000468` ! multicellular organism\n+- `UBERON:0000463` ! organism substance\n+\n+The axiom was added to `src/ontology/components/external-disjoints.obo`, matching the location identified in the issue discussion for disjointness assertions.\n+\n+## Rationale\n+\n+The issue requested that `multicellular organism` and `organism substance` be made disjoint so that classes accidentally modeled as both a whole organism and a body-derived substance become logically unsatisfiable. This supports the quality-control use case described in the issue, such as catching an incorrect equivalence between a substance class and an NCBITaxon organism class.\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+- Reviewed the imported issue context and comments.\n+- Confirmed the relevant UBERON term identifiers in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` using `obo-grep.pl`.\n+- Added the minimal `disjoint_from` axiom to the external disjoi